== 工作文化與爭議 ==
2018年，《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》對狄珍妮進行了-{zh-cn:报道; zh-hk:報道; zh-sg:报道; zh-tw:報導;}-，因為她面臨著續簽脫口秀的問題，以及探索其他創作渠道的決定，包括她的[[Netflix|Netflix]]喜劇特輯節目《Relatable》（2018年），該片惡搞了她的善良形象。當被問及匿名小報-{zh-cn:报道; zh-hk:報道; zh-sg:报道; zh-tw:報導;}-說她經常對待員工們很差時，她認為這些指控是錯誤的，她說：「我想要的一件事是每個人都能為他們工作的地方感到高興和自豪，如果不高興的話，就不要在這裡工作。」<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/12/arts/television/ellen-degeneres.html |title = Ellen DeGeneres Is Not as Nice as You Think (Published 2018) |author = Jason Zinoman |date = 2018-12-12 |publisher = The New York Times |language = en |access-date = 2021-07-27 |archive-date = 2020-10-17 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201017024155/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/12/arts/television/ellen-degeneres.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>

2020年7月，《{{link-en|BuzzFeed News|BuzzFeed News}}》-{zh-cn:报道了一些文章; zh-hk:報道了一些文章; zh-sg:报道了一些文章; zh-tw:發布了一些報導;}-，其中匿名的前員工們指責該節目是一個{{link-en|有毒職場|Toxic workplace}}，指責執行製作人有[[性騷擾|騷擾]]的行為，以及指稱有種族歧視言論和{{link-en|微冒犯|Microaggression}}的環境氣氛。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/krystieyandoli/ellen-employees-allege-toxic-workplace-culture |title = Former Employees Say Ellen's “Be Kind” Talk Show Mantra Masks A Toxic Work Culture |author = Krystie Lee Yandoli |date = 2020-07-16 |publisher = BuzzFeed News |language = en |access-date = 2021-07-27 |archive-date = 2020-07-17 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200717003612/https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/krystieyandoli/ellen-employees-allege-toxic-workplace-culture |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/krystieyandoli/ex-ellen-show-employees-sexual-misconduct-allegations |title = Dozens Of Former “Ellen Show” Employees Say Executive Producers Engaged In Rampant Sexual Misconduct And Harassment |author = Krystie Lee Yandoli |date = 2020-07-30 |publisher = BuzzFeed News |language = en |access-date = 2021-07-27 |archive-date = 2020-07-31 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200731034944/https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/krystieyandoli/ex-ellen-show-employees-sexual-misconduct-allegations |dead-url = no }}</ref>[[華納媒體|華納媒體]]開始了調查。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/ellen-degeneres-workplace-investigation-1234717494/ |title = ‘Ellen DeGeneres Show’ Workplace Under Investigation by WarnerMedia (EXCLUSIVE) |author = Matt Donnelly |date = 2020-07-27 |publisher = Variety |language = en |access-date = 2021-07-27 |archive-date = 2020-07-27 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200727211207/https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/ellen-degeneres-workplace-investigation-1234717494/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>狄珍妮向她的員工道歉，並寫道「她希望她的節目是一個『沒有人敢大聲說話，每個人都會受到尊重』的地方，而且她『得知情況並非如此，感到很失望。』」調查結束後，三位主管被解雇，他們是執行製作人Ed Glavin和Kevin Leman，以及聯合執行製作人Jonathan Norman。該節目發誓會採取措施改變這種文化；狄珍妮在2020年9月第十八季的開場時再次道歉。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.queerty.com/watch-ellen-addresses-elephant-room-season-18-premiere-20200921 |title = WATCH: Ellen addresses the elephant in the room in season 18 premiere |author = Dan Tracer |date = 2020-09-21 |publisher = Queerty |language = en |access-date = 2021-07-27 |archive-date = 2020-09-25 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200925114913/https://www.queerty.com/watch-ellen-addresses-elephant-room-season-18-premiere-20200921 |dead-url = no }}</ref>她的DJ{{link-en|史蒂芬·伯斯|Stephen "tWitch" Boss}}被晉升為聯合執行製作人，並擔任該節目的主持人，代替狄珍妮。

